  "title": "Security & Safety Guard (Warehouse)",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Job Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li>Implement and enforce Workplace Safety & Health (WSH) policies</li><li>Conduct safety inspections, risk assessments, and audits</li><li>Identify hazards and recommend corrective and preventive actions</li><li>Ensure compliance with MOM, and Singapore safety regulations</li><li>Develop and deliver safety training, toolbox talks, and inductions</li><li>Investigate accidents, incidents, and near misses and prepare reports</li><li>Maintain safety documentation, records, and reports</li><li>Coordinate with operations teams to promote safe work practices</li><li>Oversee PPE compliance and safety signage</li><li>Support emergency response planning and fire drills</li></ul><h3><strong>Job Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li>Diploma / Degree in <strong>Workplace Safety & Health, Engineering, or related field</strong></li><li><strong>WSH Officer / Coordinator certification</strong> preferred</li><li>Minimum <strong>2–3 years of safety experience</strong>, preferably in warehouse / logistics / manufacturing</li><li>Good communication and presentation skills</li><li>Able to conduct <strong>training and safety briefings</strong></li><li>Detail-oriented, proactive, and hands-on</li></ul><h3><strong>Working Arrangement</strong></h3><ul><li>6 Day Work Week (Rotating Shift: Morning & Night)</li></ul>",
